The paper deals with the effect of side information on the exact recovery problem in the binary stochastic block model, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of side information is a common theme in signal processing (cs.SI) and communication theory (cs.SY), which are related to the problem studied in the paper. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the phase transition of exact recovery, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
